Comprehensive 150-Day Action Plan to Master Java Full-Stack and Microservices Skills for Job Placement in India

 Phase 1: Foundation Building (Days 1-30)

Focus: Core Java, Spring Boot, REST APIs, and Basic Front-End

1. Days 1-15: Java Advanced Concepts
   路 Topics: Multithreading, JVM tuning, OOP, design patterns (e.g., Factory, Builder), and collections .
   路 Daily Breakdown:
     路 4 hours: Theory + coding exercises (e.g., concurrency problems).
     路 3 hours: Build small apps (e.g., inventory management CLI).
     路 3 hours: Review and debug code.
   路 Check: Implement a multithreaded task scheduler.
2. Days 16-30: Spring Boot and REST APIs
   路 Topics: Dependency injection, Spring MVC, JPA/Hibernate, RESTful services .
   路 Daily Breakdown:
     路 4 hours: Build CRUD APIs (e.g., payroll system ).
     路 3 hours: Integrate databases (H2/MySQL).
     路 3 hours: API testing (Postman/curl).
   路 Check: Create a fully functional employee management API.

 Phase 2: Microservices and Front-End (Days 31-90)

Focus: Microservices architecture, front-end technologies, and mobile compatibility.

1. Days 31-50: Microservices with Spring Cloud
   路 Topics: Service discovery (Eureka), API Gateway, Circuit Breakers (Resilience4J), distributed tracing .
   路 Daily Breakdown:
     路 4 hours: Build two microservices (e.g., user service + order service).
     路 3 hours: Implement inter-service communication (RestTemplate/Feign).
     路 3 hours: Configure Eureka server .
   路 Check: Deploy linked microservices with load balancing.
2. Days 51-70: Front-End Technologies
   路 Topics: HTML/CSS, JavaScript, TypeScript, React/Angular .
   路 Daily Breakdown:
     路 4 hours: Learn responsive UIs (e.g., Tailwind CSS ).
     路 3 hours: Build front-end components for existing APIs.
     路 3 hours: Practice TypeScript for type safety .
   路 Check: Create a React-based UI for your employee management system.
3. Days 71-90: Mobile-Compatible APIs
   路 Topics: Stateless authentication (JWT/OAuth), API security, caching (Redis) .
   路 Daily Breakdown:
     路 4 hours: Implement JWT-based auth in Spring Boot.
     路 3 hours: Optimize APIs for mobile (e.g., pagination, compression).
     路 3 hours: Add caching to improve performance.
   路 Check: Secure your APIs and test with mobile simulators.

 Phase 3: End-to-End Development (Days 91-120)

Focus: CI/CD, testing, and deployment.

1. Days 91-105: DevOps and CI/CD
   路 Topics: Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins, AWS/Azure .
   路 Daily Breakdown:
     路 4 hours: Containerize microservices (Docker).
     路 3 hours: Set up CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions/Jenkins).
     路 3 hours: Deploy to cloud platforms (e.g., AWS EC2).
   路 Check: Automate deployment for your full-stack app.
2. Days 106-120: Testing and Monitoring
   路 Topics: Unit testing (JUnit), integration testing, Micrometer monitoring .
   路 Daily Breakdown:
     路 4 hours: Write tests for all modules (TDD approach).
     路 3 hours: Implement logging and monitoring (Prometheus/Grafana).
     路 3 hours: Performance tuning.
   路 Check: Achieve 80%+ test coverage for your projects.

 Phase 4: Projects and Revision (Days 121-150)

Focus: Portfolio development, interview prep, and advanced concepts.

1. Days 121-135: Capstone Project
   路 Build an end-to-end application (e.g., e-commerce platform with microservices, React front-end, and mobile compatibility) .
   路 Daily Breakdown:
     路 5 hours: Coding and integration.
     路 3 hours: Documentation and code reviews.
     路 2 hours: Debugging and optimization.
2. Days 136-150: Interview Preparation
   路 Revise key concepts, practice DSA, and simulate interviews.
   路 Daily Breakdown:
     路 4 hours: Solve LeetCode problems (focus on Java/Spring).
     路 3 hours: Mock interviews (e.g., system design questions).
     路 3 hours: Soft skills and resume polishing .

 Weekly Routine Example

Day Time Allocation Focus Area
Monday 10 hours Core Java + Coding
Tuesday 10 hours Spring Boot APIs
Wednesday 10 hours Microservices Implementation
Thursday 10 hours Front-End Development
Friday 10 hours DevOps & Deployment
Saturday 10 hours Project Work
Sunday 5 hours Review & Planning

 Key Tips for Success

1. Consistency Over Intensity: Avoid burnout with balanced sessions .
2. Hands-On Practice: Build 3-4 portfolio projects (e.g., API-driven apps, cloud-deployed microservices).
3. Community Engagement: Join Java/Spring communities (e.g., roadmap.sh ) for support.
4. Iterative Learning: Use the "Skill Sprint" method focus on 20% of concepts that deliver 80% of results (e.g., Spring Boot for backend, React for front-end).

 Tools and Technologies to Master

路 Backend: Java 17+, Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, JPA/Hibernate
路 Frontend: React/Angular, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
路 DevOps: Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins, AWS
路 APIs: RESTful services, JWT, OAuth, GraphQL 

This plan leverages accelerated learning techniques  and industry trends  to ensure you become job-ready in 150 days. Adjust based on your progress and focus on weak areas during weekly reviews.
